						               													<description>Splade is an evolution of Spline for 3 players that can be played with a Series: Shibumi set. It uses a 4x4 holes board and spheres in 3 colors (white, black and red). It was inspired by the great Gute Nachbarn, by Alex Randolph.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to play:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The board (n&amp;times;n) starts empty.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Starting with white (then black and red), players take turns placing a marble of their colour on an empty space or platform (2&amp;times;2 arrangement of marbles).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Whenever a full line with exactly 2 colors is formed, the game ends. The winner is the player with a color in that line whose position in the player order is immediately before the other player with a color in that line.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is, for a 4&amp;times;4 set, a 4-in-a-row on the first layer, or a 3-in-a-row on the 2nd layer, or a 2-in-a-row on the 3rd layer.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Example:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;White makes a line of 3 on the second layer containing 2 white balls and one black ball and wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Variant:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Consider the colour of the previous player instead of the next.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Included in the Shibumi Rule Book&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Soft cover:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;http://www.lulu.com/shop/cameron-browne-and-nestor-romeral-andres/shibumi-rule-book/paperback/product-18940123.html&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Downloadable PDF:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;http://www.nestorgames.com/rulebooks/SHIBUMI_EN.pdf&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
